This paper deals with the cognitive radio channel with common message, which involves the transmission of both private and common messages between two transmitters and their corresponding receivers. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI), as well as signal processing (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and communication and information theory (cs.CC).
